HEADWORD: Materialist
<hw>Ma*te"ri*al*ist</hw>
<pr>(m⟦adot⟧*t⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>mat⟦eacute⟧rialiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who denies the existence of spiritual substances or agents, and
maintains that spiritual phenomena, so called, are the result of some
peculiar organization of matter. A believer in <cref>philosophical
materialism</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds to the existence of matter, as
distinguished from the idealist, who denies it.</def>
<rj><au>Berkeley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Materialistical</ent>⟦br⟧
